
[1]amalgam

   AMAL'GAM, n. [Gr. to soften. Its usual derivation is certainly
   erroneous.]

   1. A mixture of mercury or quicksilver with another metal; any metallic
   alloy, of which mercury forms an essential constituent part.

   2. A mixture or compound of different things.
